  "name": "Non-cannulated F1717 compression-bending — UQ declared, sensitivity gap (W-AL-02)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Uncertainty quantification has been performed on key material and geometric inputs; we plan to extend with sensitivity analysis in a future revision to identify dominant input drivers, but no formal sensitivity analysis artifact has been completed at this time.",
