    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters sourced from measurements with documented uncertainty; probabilistic distributions assigned to key inputs.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and ultimate tensile strength distributions derived from material certification data for the production Ti-6Al-4V lot. Geometric dimensions measured from 11 physical constructs via CMM; variability incorporated into the simulation ensemble. Uncertainty quantification performed using Monte Carlo sampling (n=500) over the joint input distribution; 95th-percentile prediction intervals reported for each QoI. Extension of this UQ work to include formal sensitivity analysis identifying the relative contribution of each input to output variance is planned for the next revision of this credibility package."
    },
